No?

1301
01:00:02,360 --> 01:00:03,159
Just no.

1302
01:00:03,159 --> 01:00:03,480
Pass.

1303
01:00:03,480 --> 01:00:04,679
Wait, we can do that?

1304
01:00:04,679 --> 01:00:05,000
Okay.

1305
01:00:07,159 --> 01:00:09,240
No, I look back up at the cliff.

1306
01:00:11,719 --> 01:00:13,719
Like Sully is so lazy.

1307
01:00:13,719 --> 01:00:18,519
He does not want to fucking climb that goddamn cliff.

1308
01:00:18,519 --> 01:00:23,079
You've moved like, I don't know, 300 feet down this river at this point, too.

1309
01:00:23,079 --> 01:00:23,480
Oh, good.

1310
01:00:23,480 --> 01:00:26,280
So I have to go 300 feet and then 20 feet vertical.

1311
01:00:26,280 --> 01:00:29,880
I mean, you could go vertical first and then 300 feet, but your call.

1312
01:00:29,880 --> 01:00:30,840
Whatever you want to do.

1313
01:00:31,720 --> 01:00:34,600
What kind of terrain am I looking at going vertical?

1314
01:00:34,600 --> 01:00:36,519
Is it like foresty or like?

1315
01:00:36,519 --> 01:00:45,480
It's like it's a rocky kind of mud, you know, river carved straight cliff face with rocks

1316
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:47,880
and roots and stuff sticking out of it.

1317
01:00:47,880 --> 01:00:48,760
All right.

1318
01:00:48,760 --> 01:00:50,200
Looks fairly scalable.

1319
01:00:50,200 --> 01:00:50,680
Okay.

1320
01:00:50,680 --> 01:00:59,880
I put my rope back into my pack and I start to scale this rocky ledge.

1321
01:01:01,640 --> 01:01:10,680
You, after a few long moments, managed to make it back up to the top.

1322
01:01:11,640 --> 01:01:19,480
And as you step up and onto the edge, you hear an echoing, cackling laugh coming out

1323
01:01:19,480 --> 01:01:21,079
and over the trees.

1324
01:01:21,079 --> 01:01:24,680
And it seems to come down and envelop you with sand.

1325
01:01:24,680 --> 01:01:25,880
Oh god, that sounds evil.

1326
01:02:00,840 --> 01:02:12,039
Fuck this game.

1327
01:02:13,079 --> 01:02:14,039
Why'd you go over the bridge?

1328
01:02:14,039 --> 01:02:16,280
You should have went over the log like we all did before.

1329
01:02:17,559 --> 01:02:19,160
Well, I forgot about that.

1330
01:02:21,160 --> 01:02:23,960
I, honest to God, had no idea where I was.

1331
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:25,720
You put me on a bridge.

1332
01:02:25,720 --> 01:02:28,360
I'm like, I should better fucking go over this bridge.

1333
01:02:29,320 --> 01:02:31,640
Can't remember if it was before or after the bridge.

1334
01:02:31,640 --> 01:02:32,440
B's were long before.

1335
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:35,320
Okay.

1336
01:02:35,320 --> 01:02:37,000
Well, yes, I should have.

